Management of Urban Environment
* The Ministry shall, for the management of urban environment, advise as may be
<\li1>
	* land use planning and management including zoning;
	* management of the construction industry in pivotal urban centres;
	* management of housing settlements;
	* management of wastes;
	* pollution control including land, water, air and noise pollution;
	* other necessary environmental management.

Conservation of Natural Resources and Cultural Heritages
* The relevant Government departments and Government organizations shall, in
	* forest resources;
	* land resources;
	* fresh water resources including underground water;
	* mineral resources;
	* agricultural resources;
	* fisheries resources;
	* marine resources;
	* natural ecosystems;
	* natural areas, wildlife, natural plants and biological diversity;
	* other natural resources stipulated by the Union Government.
